title: Grandkids & my kids love them! Bought 16 for Xmas!
text: Every year I seem to buy something that ends up being a family gift. This was 2021.  I bought 5 for my kids & 11 for my grandkids. I‚Äôm buying myself one next.  Technically I bought 17, but mine was damaged. I returned it & I just have not reordered it yet bc I truly cannot choose which design I want now. There are so many choices.  It was nice to be able to buy an owl for one grandkid, unicorns for others, & dinosaurs & dragons too.  While input based 5 identical lights for my 5 kids that say I love you to the moon & back I did not duplicate a single grandchild‚Äòs design. They each have their own unique lamp & they absolutely love them.

title: All 5 kids (21-35) loved them!
text: I bought these for my 5 kids who are scattered around the US bc this is what I have said to them for literally decades.  Every single kid without failed loved it. Then I bought a similar light for each of my grandkids as these were sold out.  The grandkids were tickled too.

title: Fanciness over functionality- my pair anyways.
text: [[VIDEOID:fe0ded02cc8947de907313d213474717]] These are pretty, but the obvious design flaw is the extremely sharp scrolled bits that I‚Äôve already cut my fingers on several times.  If they had curved the scroll back into itself instead of outwards it probably would have been okay, but as it is it both snags all of your fabrics & threads, but also tears your skin if you aren‚Äôt extremely careful.  So if I keep them I will either cover the sharp tips with glue, file them down, or use a soldering iron to reshape that part of the metal if I can find out if it‚Äôs safe to solder that type of metal.  The other issue I had is that the blades rub together as you can clearly see in the pics as it‚Äôs leaving marks on the metal.  As I intended to use these as embroidery snips I only need to open the scissors a tiny amount so it‚Äôs not terribly awful, but it does limit what I can do with these scissors as I had hoped to also use them for appliqu√©.  They are pretty & I like the overall design, but the manufacturer needs to fix the handles where the sharp parts are because it‚Äôs damaging to your expensive supplies & your body.  I have large hands for a girl which was the main reason I picked these bc I saw the handles appeared to have larger openings for the hands & they do.  As it has a screw holding the blades together I might try to adjust them to get the blades to be more fluid & not rub together & not dig into each other, but so far it just looks like the engineering is a hair off. The angles of the blades appear as though they will rub even after adjusting.  I hope not because other than what I‚Äôve stated I like them.  They have a couple of design flaws, but I‚Äôm hoping I can work my way around them.

title: Arrived Dead.

title: Nice leash, but I hate the snap!
text: I bought this specifically so yhst when my adorable grandkids walk my dogs and theirs they don‚Äôt drag our other very expensive 6 foot long leashes o. He ground and running mnhhem by fraying them. I live on a budget so making things last and jerking then pretty and I‚Äôm working order is a big deal to me. The fraying breaks my other leashes down and loosens the weave that makes them strong. I love these leashes. They are the perfect length for waking gigs and making them heel right next to you. The bungee part allows them to step off the sidewalk and go their business in the grass. I like them so much I now have 2 with 1 red and 1blue. The only hbu g I‚Äôm not grilled about is the bolt on the end.  They have a spring that renders them useless sometimes on other products I‚Äôve purchased.  I would normally and probably should return this product now yhst I can see what type of snap/bolt they use, but I am disabled and returns that I have to drive to ups are a pain in the butt, but since this snap is functional I will use it until it eventually quits working and then I will take the bungee leash apart and replace the snap and continue up use it because the rest of it is very well made.  I purchaed it to Ide with my daughter Samantha‚Äôs husky/German Shepherd mixed dog who is still a puppy and does not know his own strength. He tends to pull on the leash in training and I was hoping to avoid that in the future due to my disabilities that include pins and rods holding my back together.  The bungee part of the leash  gives me enough notice to brace for impact when Bjkrn decides to try to bolt after bunnies and my grandkids. He‚Äôs just a big old baby that wants to have fun and I‚Äôm a broken grandma trying to hang on!  Lol. This leash allows me to do that without risk of further injuries!

title: Pleasantly Surprised
text: I am surprised at how well these work. I strung them across some wooden posts in my backyard in mid-afternoon, straight out of the box. The "on-off" button is a little strange, because it's a push button - not a switch - and there is no way to tell if you're turning them off or on. Other than that minor annoyance, these work beautifully. I get up at 0500 for work, and after that first day I hung the lights up, I awoke for work and glanced out the window, totally shocked to see the lights still brightly glowing. I'm going to be purchasing a few more strands of these. If you're on the fence - get 'em! Keep in mind they are glass, so ensure they are secured if over a hard surface like a patio.

title: Mine only lasted a year
text: I purchased the LED outdoor Lithonia dusk to dawn security Area/wall light  for my home. It was supposed to last like 100000 hours and had a 5 year warranty. I had it professionally hung by an electrician. It was wonderful and made me feel secure while it lasted..but the light only stayed on for a year. It hangs at the high end peak of my house and we have been unable to reach it. Yesterday, while having electrician here for other work as well, I was able to have an electrician troubleshoot it to see if the problem was with the light or wiring. He informed me that the light itself is bad as the power is reaching it. How do I get it replaced since it is under warranty? The model is the: OLW 23 or 31 (it's paperwork says both numbers). He took the one not working down, but I did not have one to replace it with. I will now have to pay again to have a replacement put back up. I have a couple other Lithonia lights around my home that were put up before this one that are still going strong. But this one I definitely did not get my moneys worth out of. I have the light in the garage if you can tell me who to contact.

title: All the old negative feedback for this item is still true.  All could be easily corrected.
text:
All the old negative feedback for this item is still true. They all should and could be easily corrected.

1) Item not a 12" square it is an 11 7/8" square. So item is not as described. Correct item's title or cut plastic to 12" square.

2) Permanent sticker is affixed to the smooth side of the item resulting in a lot of unnecessary work to remove label. I carefully used heat gun to soften glue. After peeling off label, used Goo Gone to removed last of glue. Label should be affixed to the textured side of item, peel off plastic, or bag.

3) Unprotected smooth side of item scuffed in transit. Item should be bagged or peel off plastic sheet with label attached. Bag would protect smooth side from scuffing and eliminate need to remove label.

title: Two easy fixes made rasp file a 5 rating for me.
text:
The rasp file needs a handle to be comfortable to use. Made one from a 4.5 inch section of rubber hose with inner diameter of 3/4 inch. To insert the rasp file in handle, with curved side of hose down on flat surface, compress with heel of palm, as rasp file is inserted into hose. When released, handle firmly grips rasp file.

Filed off edge rows of rasp teeth so they would not scratch work when using the files. Gently and slowly running the rasp file edges between thumb and index finger then index finger over the file will confirm all the burrs removed. Mine had two burrs at the corners at the ends of the flat file.

title: Great kit. Worked wonderfully for cat6e
text:
I bought this to repair a handful of cables that were damaged. Also I needed to relocate some integrated wall cabling. Worked perfectly.
My only suggestion is make sure you have the cable the right direction. It was user error ar first that the cable wasn't working. Took a couple tries, so make sure to leave yourself extra cable or make a test cable first.
Plenty of ends included, and using this was much easier than expected.

Just know you are getting what you are paying for.

title: We have terribly hard water so it's not a 3 year set for us, but it's a good value.
text:
I change my filters about every 4-5 months so this doesn't work out to be a 3 year set for me, but it is still a great value and it works very very well.
The taste of pure clean RO, just can't be beat.
Highly recommend!

title: Beautiful lights!
text:
High quality and easy to setup and use.
I already had Kasa setup for the other 20+ smart switches and lights in our house and this was a great addition. We got 2 sets to run on our living room... Cause who doesn't need more RGB in their life. There are lots of cool settings by default and the ability to customize really makes them great.
Plus being able to say "Hey Google, Dance Party" is just a blast for the kids.

title: High tolerance made my door rub when shutting, some won't even close.
text:
Ended up returning these after installing on 4 doors. EVERY single one had issues closing after installation. They seem ok when putting on until you go to close the door and if you have a reasonable new house the clearance for hinge tolerance isn't very high to create a better seal. Well if you use these overpriced hinges you won't be able to close the door afterwards.
I found another brand name, higher quality hinge for quite a bit less. DON'T Waste your money on these. This is the 4th amazon basics product I am HIGHLY DISSATISFIED with. When they first started putting out their Amazon Basics line it was a good value for the money. Now it's just another bait for amazon to make a quick buck off of terribly designed products.
Avoid at all costs!

title: High quality great fit
text: I have bought 2 of these packs and they work great. I wear a mask about 6-10 times then discard for a new one. They fit wonderfully and look good in black.

title: Easy to install, very quiet, wish it pushed a bit more air
text:
Even in my small bathroom you hardly hear this thing. It's a huge step up from our original fans you could hear on the other side of the house. My only complaint is that it still has a hard time keeping up with humidity from the shower. It still works pretty well and for the noise level I will take it. I just leave it running for about 30 minutes after the shower and it is good to go.
About the same as the old one there and It's not a distraction through the whole house, which is why it's still 5 stars!

title: I have wasted my money
text: I received these yesterday and picked one to wear to work today.  They are light weight.  I didn‚Äôt notice a nose piece.  There is a small piece at the bridge of the nose to fit the mask to your face, but it is real thin.  I had to adjust the mask on my face multiple times.  The top of the mask repeatedly  went up into my lower eyelids.  I had to switch masks within 1/2 hour of putting it on.  The constant adjusting and going into my eyes was unbearable.  Very uncomfortable.  I have worn multiple masks over the past 3 years.  This is definitely one of the worst.  I can‚Äôt use the rest of them.  I basically paid a high price for a mask I wore 1/2 hour.

title: Uncomfortable

title: Pleased

I needed new vent grates for my home. I searched around and discovered what type I would need. I just ordered one, in case I wasn‚Äôt pleased.

The grate arrived. I was happy with the quality. I just dropped it into the vent opening to install it. Easy, Peasy.

It made a difference in the look of the room. I will be ordering more.

title: We finally put it together
text:
I saw a post for this in a Facebook group, and decided to purchase it. It sat in my dining room for a couple weeks. I finally put it together and was happy I did.

The main negative for me was that the numbers have adhesive backs. You choose the numbers you need, and stick them on the light. It can be difficult for some people to get them on straight.

The address plaque is solar powered. There is a switch to turn the plaque on. You can choose between a warm light or a cool light.

Easy to assemble. Stays lit for hours. We were pretty impressed.

title: Great concept, average useage
text:
These do beat the old face shields. They have a much clearer view. They are more comfortable.

There is a film over both sides of the shield. The tabs located to pull the film off, doesn‚Äôt work. I have to use another type of tape I had around the house, that had more stickiness to get the film off.

The face shield is easy to put together. If you put a new shield on the glasses, the tabs that hold the shield in place don‚Äôt work as well. The shield after comes off the glasses. This also makes it difficult to store or transport the face shield. You don‚Äôt want to take it apart, because it won‚Äôt stay together well, afterwards.

title: Great stuff
text: liner cover up dings, scratches and old wall paper.  I wanted to paper the powder room but didn't want to go through the hassle of stripping off old wall paper.  Read the reviews, especially the ones which had helpful tips and decided to give it a go.  The wall liner worked as advertised and the tips were more than useful.  The tips for how to cut the liner were a life saver.  So read up, get a sharp blade, the break away blade knife worked best for me.  I snapped off the old blade and had a fresh new one for each cut.  And it is best to cut from the middle to the edge.  It was like wall papering the powder room twice, but it did save a lot of prep work.  Would buy again.

Blue molded police officers engaged in different poses, about the same size as your typical army man.  Also comes with a little plastic police car (so-so), itty bitty traffic cones and a tank.  Relatively inexpensive, the policemen will last a lot longer than the car or tank, but it was the policemen I was looking for to begin with and they are sturdy enough to last a good long while.

title: Great deal and they are soooo sooo adorable in person
text: I already had the squirrel that I purchased at my local Dollar General. I paid $10 + tax. Here I got all four with no tax which equals out to a little bit over $6 for each. Great deal and they are soooo sooo adorable in person. They light up quite nice.

title: Probably one of the nicest aviator glasses in the market today!
text: These are really nice aviator glasses. A little too large for me (I got the 57 mm), but my husband absolutely adores them. He drives for a living and these glasses help tremendously with the glare and the late afternoon Florida sun while he is behind the wheel. Perfect fit, do not rub on his nose bridge and are really good looking glasses as well. Highly recommend!

title: For the money you can't go wrong!
text: I am a single female in my sixties who has had a load of hand me down tools over the years in my garage. Some of them are rusted and just not good to use, so when I saw this set I just had to try it. It comes in a little cloth case (not super impressive from a gift giving perspective) and has a variety of 5 tools. The pliers were something I definitely needed and for my needs, this set is perfect. Highly recommend!

title: Cute and fashionable pathway lights
text: I really liked these for use on my walkway near my door. They are not super bright, but are more decorative and a means to help guide your path in the dark. They were super easy to put together and after putting them on the walkway, that night I had light where I didn't have it before. I love that I can almost have these flush to the ground so they don't interfere with my garden plants too. I love the design and the brushed nickel highlights. Highly recommend if you are looking for a decorative way to lighten your walkway.

title: Great facemasks for small children
text: These are nice disposable face masks at a reasonable price. I have two grandchildren (ages 5 and 7) who I got these to keep in my house for when they visit. They are probably not 100% the best in the market for protection against the virus, but they are a perfect size and easy to wear (which ensures they will keep them on for long periods of time). They fit well and I have heard no complaints about heat or any other issues when they wear them. I like the fact that they are individually wrapped as well as it keeps the masks clean up until use.

title: Great lighting addition to any home!
text: I have had my handyman install these in my living room tray ceiling (I wouldn't even begin to think of doing this myself). I love the way they look and I will be using them for parties and get togethers for many years to come (of course, after this pandemic). The remote control works great and makes it easy to change colors, appearances and moods at the simple touch of a button. Highly recommend!

title: Colorful and fun for night time!
text: This is super cute. I have two grandsons (ages 3 and 6) and when I set this up in their room they really loved it. Stars magically appear on the ceiling and walls and the white noise feature is a great addition (helps them sleep longer with less middle of the night wake ups). Highly recommend this to everyone. This also would make a great baby shower gift (something no one else would think of).

title: Nice adapter, does the job, but is large
text: Not overly thrilled with this travel plug. I am rating it as 4 stars as I feel there is nothing wrong with the adapter, I just don't care for it as much as others that I own. To me, it is overly big. The plug does not retreat into the unit which seems to make it even larger to try to pack. Maybe I am just picky, but I prefer the travel adapters where the are more compact.

title: Broke when trying to assemble
text: Maybe this was just the model we received but in trying to assemble the lamp one of the arms immediately cracked off and we were unable to use it.  Honestly can't review it but I will say it had a cute shade and base and would have looked great in my guess bedroom if I could have used it.

title: Great headlights that are bright and useful!
text: These are super cute and super useful. I have worn one when walking the dog during the winter months (when it gets dark so early) and this little device really lights up the road for me (and makes me visible to drivers). I also gave one to my son who jogs and rides bikes also at night and he told me that it was great to use where he is (California in the desert area where there are critters that roam at night). I also have two grandchildren that have tried these while they were camping in a backyard tent and they got such a hoot out of them. Probably the best $15 I have ever spent for safety, utility and fun!

title: Great device to set up and use!!!!! A must have!!!
text: This SUNYE Outdoor Smart Timer and Dimmer is a great device. I set it up earlier this week to use with my outdoor lights and decorations for Christmas. As an fyi, I have only one outside plug and it is situated behind a bunch of shrubbery. It is not easy to get to and I would struggle every time I would have to plug and unplug decorations. Now with a simple voice command to Alexa or even setting up the lights on a timer, I don't have to go in and out of my house to turn lights on or off. And this was super easy to set up and pair with my Alexa device. I am 60 something years old and sometimes can be technically challenged. I had no trouble at all setting this up. I highly recommend!

title: Great filter system for use in the shower!!!
text: I live in a relatively new construction home in Central/Coastal Florida. When I moved in, I was warned of having hard water and was told by neighbors that I should probably invest in a whole house water system. Of course, although that would have been great, finances just would not allow it. I started using spray on water repellent on my shower doors to help prevent spotting and so far it has been ok. When I saw this filter I thought I would try it. It was easy to install and actually works. In addition to now not having to worry about water spots in the shower any longer, I now also reap the benefit of better, filtered water for my hair and body (and no chlorine). Although I still have the hard water issues in the rest of the house, my showers (I purchased another for my second bathroom) no longer are an issue. I highly recommend this relatively inexpensive filter for every home!

title: Great indoor plant light bulb!
text: This is a perfect grow light for inside plants. I always start my vegetables and flower seedlings inside and I look for a strong, clean plant light that I can put on a timer. This is super bright but an LED variety so it is far more economical and will last longer than standard bulbs. Highly recommend!

title: Great LED light bulb for your home
text: Great LED light bulb. Clear and very bright. I love LED lights for my entire home as they are energy efficient and last far longer than traditional bulbs. If you are looking for replacement bulbs, I recommend Wiyifada bulbs, reasonably priced and good quality.

title: Easy to use and works great to light my home overnight!
text: I purchased a new home in Florida less than a year ago. It came standard with outside lights (including a few by the garage) that all manually had to be turned on to be active. As my neighborhood is not blessed with a lot of street lighting, it can be really dark at night around here. When I saw these I wasn't sure how it would work, but boy was I surprised! I love that the two lights which are on the outsides of my garage doors now go on (on their own) each night and shut off each morning. I no longer need to remember to manually put them on. 60 watts is perfect for me, not overly bright but enough to see footing to my walkway. Highly recommend for anyone who wants a sensored lighting for the perimeter of their home.

title: Great Alexa-enabled light switch!
text: Great 3 way light switch. My house definitely is Alexasized, with many devices (including vacuum and thermostat) connected. When I saw this, I thought it would be great for my bedroom and I was not disappointed. This is a great way for me to change the brightness of my 3 way bulb to help me go from low light to a reading light by just calling out a demand. I did have some difficulty setting it up, but I stuck with it and managed to get it wired and connected to Alexa. I consider myself somewhat technically-challenged so don't take my difficulty as common. I don't know what I would do without my smart devices, certainly has made my life so much easier (and fun). Highly recommend!

title: Great solar powered lights at a reasonable price!
text: For the money these lights are fantastic. I live in a fairly dimly lit community and although crime is minimal I prefer to have some sense of security at night. Being solar powered, I was able to set these up easily myself (without have to call in an electrician). These work great and I have them spaced strategically around the perimeter of my home. They are bright, but not blinding, and the solar battery charge keeps them active all night long. I highly recommend these as an added security feature for your home (at a minimal cost).

title: Great mini-flashlight that really works!
text: This is a great mini-flashlight. I use it every morning attached to my dog's leash for my pre-dawn walks. Little, compact, but packs a punch when it comes to the brightness. I have ordered another one to keep in my car's glovebox to use when I am on the road. I highly recommend this portable light for anyone who wants a small compact flashlight that is light and easy to carry anywhere.

title: Just what I was looking for!!!
text: I moved into a newly constructed house last September and have never been happy with the water pressure or the shower head that came with the house (including the fact that I upgraded). I guess the water pressure was already low (intentionally as a water saving item in the house) and the existing head was too small. Once I replaced it (and it was super easy for me to do), I was able to remove the water saving washer and now I have a great, strong, full head shower device which works wonderfully. I also ordered one for the guest bathroom as well. For the price, this is a great shower head. Highly recommend.

title: No remote but overall good attractive lighting
text: I was looking for something I could use over my kitchen cabinets and these fit the bill. Works well, I can dim the lights so they are attractive on the overnight (giving me a night-light appearance in my kitchen). There is no remote control which makes it inconvenient for me to have to turn these on and off (which is why I am deducting a star). But if not having a remote is not an issue for you, then I highly recommend this light strip to you.

title: Nice large shower head, good water pressure (finally)
text: I have to start by saying I bought a brand new construction last year in northern Florida. Part of my selections was fixtures in the kitchen and bath. I selected top notch choices, but I was not thrilled with the shower head (it was your typical smaller round head with low water pressure over all). When I saw this rainfall shower head I had to have it. I was not daring enough to do the install myself so I hired a local handyman to do it. It was easy-peasy (for him) and I loved the end result. No longer am I in a small spray area, this rainfall head gives amazing coverage and is powerful. I am thrilled with this shower head now. No complaints, just all good comments here.

title: Great lights that look perfect in my home!
text: These LED bulbs go great in my new dining room rectangular long farmhouse style chandelier. They dim perfectly and have a nice clean clear color to them and they don't get hot. They should last a long time (according to the box) and I am very happy with them. Highly recommend for anyone looking for an LED alternative light!

title: Decent fan, but I got a defective model
text: Overall, this is a nice, quiet, small sized ceiling fan. I put it out on my lanai here in Florida and it's only been out there for a few weeks, so I can't speak to how it will hold up to the humidity. I am deducting 3 stars from this review because the fan I got was defective on one of the blade frames. I couldn't screw the blade into the frame on two of the three screwholes. It was like they were stripped. Anyway, one of my blades only has one screw holding it on the frame. Not sure if anyone else had this problem. I tried using tape to secure it, but not sure if it will hold. I had my neighbor take a look at it and he told me it is defective. Anyway, I just hope, while it's running someday, the blade doesn't fly off as a projectile if it loosens. Poor workmanship for sure.

title: Fantastic Smart Plug
text: First, I have to mention I have several smart devices that work with Alexa in my house. This is my first Geeni product for same. I had no issues setting it up (unlike some other reviewers) and I can be technology impaired. This works like a gem and I keep it in my bedroom not only for me to activate the light but also for the nightlight feature. If there is a negative it's because it's not made in the USA. But outside of that, it is reasonably priced and works great.

title: Great candles for indoor or outdoor decorations, easily controlled, look great (and real)!
text: These are really great remote controlled 'candles'. I put them on my porch outside (I live in Florida and have a screened lanai). These are colorful and look like authentic candles. I love that I can control these from inside the house with the remote. I have gotten a lot of compliments since I have received them and at least one person (my sister) asked me where I got them and asked for the link. These are impressivd and look super real. Highly recommend!

title: Great holiday lighting set
text: These are a great little set of lights. Planning to use them to decorate my fireplace or my stairwell. Took them out of the box to try them out. Lot's of nice options for twinkling, well constructed and they appear that they will last several seasons. As of today these are listed for over $200. Must be a mistake as one can get something similar at Walmart for less than $20. Anyhow, for around $20, you would have a great set of lights for your tree or home decor this year at Christmas.

title: Another great Waterpik product!
text: This is a great Waterpik for your home. Beautifully designed, it ergonomically fits in your hand and has 6 modes of pulsing to help relieve pain and sore muscles. Also streams water powerfully to assist in your showering and cleanups. The best part of this was it was so easy for me to install. I had an older version in my bathroom and I was hoping that i could do this myself (without having to drag in my significant other to assist). I easily was able to replace my existing one with hardly any issues, and I am technically challenged to say the least! I love the way this looks in my shower and it makes my bath look like I gave it a makeover! This Waterpik model has a great price, too, which makes it an affordable luxury as well.

title: Great modern look, a little difficult to install for the technically-challenged woman I am!
text: I honestly love the idea of this. Modern, sleek and lasts a lot longer than typical floodlight bulbs that I use around my house. I tried to install this myself in my bedroom, and I have to admit it took me quite a while. I am not a technical person by any means and usually screwing in the lightbulb is about the extent of my capabilities, lol. However, once I was able to figure this out, the second one was an easier install. I think it also made it harder since my ceilings are relatively high and I was trying to do all this on a ladder. Next time they go out (which hopefully won't be for quite a while), I may get a handyman to do it for me. They look great though!

title: Great powerful little light and personal electrical charger!
text: Great little light to keep around for emergencies or for those who go camping. I love the fact that for the size of this, the amount of light dispersed is absolutely amazing and it will run for up to 12 hours on a single charge. To be able to charge my I-phone is just icing on the cake. I live in Florida and love that I will now be able to charge my phone during storm related power outages. I will agree with others that I am wondering about the ability to change the lithium battery once it wears down. I can't see spending almost $40 for a flashlight/charger that may only last a year or two. I need to do further research on the batter, I went to the CAT website where they discuss the product but still don't see anything where you can replace the battery. Maybe it's meant to be semi-disposable?

title: Great new technology!
text: Let me start by saying that I, personally, did not install this. I have a handy man who comes here occasionally and I had him hook it up for me. According to him, this dimmer seemed a little more complex to install than others, said there was a lot more wiring. I actually downloaded the software to my IPhone from the ITunes store and got ready for the light when he finished. I was really impressed at how easily this is to use. I even set the time for sunset and set the light to 37% so now I won't be coming home in the dark any longer! No complaints, just really impressed how easy it was for me to use and learn.

title: Great gadget, does the job for a price
text: I don't have a lot to add as to what others have said. I found this unit extremely easy and accurate to use in determining where I can successfully mount a wall television in my bedroom. I also have a Zircon wall scanning unit and in comparison, this Bosch is much easier to use and I think I can rely on it more. On the downside, it is pricey, but as a gadget for the homeowner who has everything, this truly fits the bill. Easy to use, detects through walls easily and accurately. I agree with other users. It would make more sense not using batteries in this as is, since my use for it will be sporadic and I think battery use will be wasteful. I think either an attached powerpack battery that you can plug in to charge prior to use would be more economical and far more useful in my opinion.

title: I love this power center!
text: This is a cool little gadget I bought to help give me some additional outlet space when my kids come over. I love the fact that I turned my two outlet wall unit into one of 6 and on top of it, I can charge my iPhone and iPad at the same time! Great little shelf to hold the phone (so it cannot get spilled on the countertop. This is a great little device!

title: Great cordless way to clean up around the outside!!!
text: To begin with, I have been using a leaf blower which is electric for the past 4 or so years. I hated the fact that every time I went to use it I had to set up the extension cords and I never could really complete the job due to the length of my driveway. And, yes, I often thought of buying a gas powered one, but I hate the idea of keeping gasoline in my garage at all times. In comes the 40 volt Lithium-Ion battery-powered Dewalt Brushless Blower and I have to admit I absolutely love it! First I am no longer tethered to my electrical outlet and I can move at ease anywhere I chose to use it. I also don't have t worry about storing gasoline as this runs on a battery. Right out of the box, the Dewalt delivered flawlessly. Quick, long-lasting charge, the Dewalt quickly and effortlessly did my driveway, walkway and even my patio (several hours of usage). I have no complaints about the Dewalt. It is powerful and relatively quiet, and gets the job done quickly (without needing to maneuver around a power cord). I absolutely love this!!!!

title: Beautiful lamp for a girl's room
text: This is the perfect lamp to doll up a little princess' bedroom. Beautiful pink shade, well made, sturdy attractive bright white base and a good size for a nightstand, this lamp is a great compliment to a girlie-girl's room. I would not recommend this for am adult's room unless the color perfectly matches the decor (and if there is a husband involved he really likes the color pink). This lamp is truly meant for a girl and it will not disappoint.

title: Great wrench, does what it needs to do
text: I found the Black & Decker MSW100 wrench to do exactly what it needs to do. Being a woman, and somewhat 'tool illiterate' I found it easy to use and fits well in my small hands. The only downside is the size, that if you are using it for something lodged in a small space you will need to get a smaller model for sure. Other than that, it's built well, comfortable fitting and priced right to the market.

title: Great Flexible Flashlight!
text: When I ordered this flashlight, I wasn't quite sure what to expect. I had been looking at tripod flashlights, but I didn't know which one was the best for the money. Now that I have used this 3 & 1 Stanley Tripod Flashlight, I don't think I could ever live without it! My first was for use in my garage. I had a garage door chain which was off the track. I set up the tipod and used the rotating head to shine the light on the exact spot I was working on. I honestly don't think I could have finished the job in the shaded darkness of a closed garage (even with the ceiling light on) without this Stanley. I recommend this for all women who will attempt to do many home repairs by themselves. I can see where I will be using this flashlight quite often because of it's maneuverability and flexibility!

title: Recessed lighting LED, set of 20
text: Recessed LED lights, set of 20.  We have a very small kitchen and 4 recessed lights.  Our old LED recessed lights, approximately 10 years old, began to fail and we purchased these as replacements.  We replace all LED lights in a series (like in the kitchen) at once - even if only one is failing - as in this case.  I am VERY disappointed in these.  First, they are a fraction of the weight of the old ones - quality?  I know things 'improve' with time- sometimes getting lighter in weight, but in this case - NO.  We installed them and in the process discovered they have 4 light brightness/color settings.  The lower wattage you go, the more 'yellow' the lights become.  Now for the real kicker - and kiss of death - they strobe or flicker or phase in and out - whatever phrase you want to call it.  When on the brightest setting, every 4 seconds - on the dimmest setting every 15 seconds.  I get migraines over such flickering - so they are junk to us.  I have read other reviews complaining about these since purchasing and a lot are suggesting you MUST install a 'dimmer' switch to control the flicker!  That is not an option in our kitchen as we have dual light switches.  But even if it was, I would return them.  The old ones didn't flicker. Our house is completely LED and NONE of them flicker.  So, they are being returned flat out.  BEWARE.  If you purchase these they are probably going to flicker - if that doesn't bother you, fine.  If it does, as with most folks, do not purchase these.  I cannot recommend these to anyone for any reason.  Having said all of this, I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful. title: chair leg covers
text: We just installed a bunch of new vinyl flooring where carpet had been. So, instead of the plastic nubs that help you slide on carpet, you need to switch to the felt based tips.  We've been through a whole passel of felt squares - our chairs have 1 1/4" square legs.  The felts with the stickers just slide off and never stay in place.  I never tried the "tack" on or screw on types for fear of harming my floor - and then we found these!  These are a really good design.  They are different than other silicone sleeve with the felt squares only at the bottom... those slip and tear the silicone, eventually coming off.  SO FAR - these have stayed in place perfectly, without slipping.  Key is that the felt square rounds UP the side of silicone sock.  Slides A LOT better across the floor as you're sitting on the chair than any of the other stick on felts.  Having said all of this, I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful.  Time will tell if these are as good as they seem to be.  We have four chairs so we used 16 tips and you get 24.  So there are replacements should they become necessary.  I think it's important that they fit snugly on the chair feet so measuring is important.  If you're tired of changing your chair foot felts, I say give this one a try.  They have multiple colors to choose from too.

title: medium duty acetylene cutting system
text: Husband needed a shop replacement and chose this one.  It's for light to medium duty use.  He reports it works as it should.  I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful.

title: square chair slides
text: Be careful when ordering these and look at measurements.  They are super small.  Our chair legs are 1 1/4" wide - that is the measurements for the OUTSIDE of these tips.  The legs you are trying to cover will need to be 3/4" or smaller.  Yikes.  I am really disappointed.

title: KN95 individually wrapped masks
text:
These are the first KN95 mask that I have ever tried that I felt like actually fit and sealed my face. They are as comfortable as a mask can be. In this era of "double masking" I did invest in a silicone frame to try and keep the mask from touching my mouth as I breathe - but these say well away from from your mouth as you breath and talk. They do a really good job "sealing" too. How can I tell? My reading glasses don't fog up.
The other thing I love, they are individually wrapped. I feel like I am getting a fresh, clean mask out of the box every time.
Bummer is they are too expensive. Wish they were back to pre-pandemic prices. But perhaps some day. In the mean time, I am biting the bullet and buying these.
I chose the white. I did not have to adjust the ear piece for a snug, proper fit.
I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful.

title: silicone face cover frames
text: I just received these and haven't used them fully yet... but a couple of things.  These happen to fit my face perfectly.  I read another review that complained it created "gaps" under their eyes - I think it must have been the particular mask they were using and/or the silicone frame wasn't fitting properly.  We are all different, I think I lucked out.  I haven't decided if I will use double sided tape or tack them into my masks for "busy" use - but when I am sitting here just testing them out with my various masks and now the double masking process - the frame sits solidly in my mask and while I am not talking, it seems to be staying in place without any tape or tacking.  It may be different if you're talking a lot or moving your head a lot.  I also read a review that said the frame was too heavy and they couldn't keep their mask on... that is an ear adjustment issue I think.  I have not had that issue.  I plan to wash them on the top rack of my dishwasher as others have noted they have done this without any problems.  Having said all of that, I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful.  All in all, these really help me to feel less claustrophobic in my mask by keep the mask away from my mouth while breathing.  Look, ultimately the whole reason to mask/double mask is to protect yourself and others from the virus. You gotta wear your masks properly.  If these don't fit your face, definitely don't use them. I personally think because they are reusable they are worth the expense and effort to see if they will work for you.  If you don't mind your mask touching your mouth, you probably don't need them.  We've got to wear them to reduce the variants and bring the pandemic to an end!  Here's to working together to get this done!

title: under cabinet light strip
text:
I purchased a longer version of just this from a different seller... but sadly they sensor didn't work on either of two. But I really loved the idea of these, so I rolled the dice on this version. I purchased 2 sets as I had before. I have to admit these are really too short (only about 1') BUT the sensors worked! The timer is a bit off, but it's close enough and as I mentioned, the sensor works perfectly. They are super easy to install - however, getting the non stick paper off to reveal the sticky part was a bit of a trick as the the non stick wanted to lift off with the sticky part - had to work a bit on that. Once I got the non- stick part of the tape off, stuck the light strip under my bathroom cabinet and set the sensor. There is a circular magnet piece to attach the sensor to. It's sort of a weaker magnet, but it works. The sensor is the rechargeable piece. So, once it needs to be charged, you just unplug the sensor, charge it and reinstall.
PROS.... really easy to install. Sensors are effective.
CONS... sensor magnet could be a lot stronger.. the nonstick part of the sticky tape was too hard to peel apart without lifting the sticky section.
Can't really rate on this.. but I wish the light string was about 1' longer.
I've had the strip up and running for about a week - so far, so good. I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful.

title: light strip
text:
Wow. There isn't much positive to say about these light strips other than the return and refund was easy! Sadly it would have been such a cool look.
They were easy to set up. The sticky strip worked well and I feel it would have probably stayed up. The problems lay with the sensor/battery unit. They didn't work. When I say "they" - I purchased 2. So, I charged them fully. Set one light strip up and plugged in. Note: the sensor/battery has a circular magnet to attach to wall or whatever you have to apply. I liked that as you need to recharge. But, the light came on and wouldn't turn off. Even though I had set for 15 seconds and night only. I charged up and tried again. Now the light won't come on at all. So because I had already stuck the strip up I thought I'd try the sensor/battery pack of the other set in case one was bad. Nope. Neither worked. One of the sensors would work in pitch black - but only about 2 out of 10 tries. All in all, the other reviews that stated the sensors were bad - were right. Dang it. Cause it would be so cool if they worked! Needless to say, I just returned them. Going to look for some with better quality. Here's to hoping. In the meantime, I would NOT buy these.

title: waterfall faucet
text:
[[VIDEOID:a9acf5d63a0f761d3938fa7867aec297]] UPDATE BELOW
I just put in a vessel type sink in my bathroom and had chosen a more spout pour faucet. The problem was the water would splash over the front edge of the sink. When we tried to reduce the pressure of the water, it wasn't enough pressure to rinse. So, I purchased this style. The waterfall effect "fans" the water so there is less of a "hose" stream of water and while we did slightly lower the pressure, the water now stays in the sink. In addition, the faucet is quite lovely. I was worried it was a bit too modern, but it looks very nice with the brushed satin texture and the oval shape that matches my vessel sink and the beveled edge mirror above it. It's actually quite a nice look. Also the faucet itself is quite weighty - I hope this equates with quality. The previous faucet was super loud too - like a jet plane taking off... this one is quite pleasant, sounds like water, not a jet plane. Those are all the pros... there were a couple of "cons" I've noticed so far... the water doesn't stop immediately... it's sort of slowly stops pouring. I didn't see any where to adjust for this so I am hoping it won't end up a dripper or leaker. The other is that the hoses that were included with faucet were WAY too short. title: set of 2 smaller flashlights
text:
UPDATE BELOW...Initially I was thinking these were pretty good... but as I use them I am finding some disappointing behavior. Mostly that the on/off toggle at the base of the flashlight is wonky. Sometimes it works... other times not. I end up shaking it. Then it comes on. This has been the case on both flashlights. Now, my original post was rejected because I mentioned some broken plastic tubing in the packaging... I wonder if that has anything to do with the glitchy issues I am having. Cannot say, but it is suspect. In my original review I included a pic of the broken pieces, but I will skip those this time. They are black metal. You pull the neck out to tighten or widen the beam. I am a bit disappointed in the overall quality - ie: the toggle failure - shake to get to turn on. I was purchasing these to replace old ones that did the same! The batteries (NOT included) go in the bottom, twist tight to function. The lens piece was very loose on both - it twists off - so I tightened those too. There is a wrist band attached - I don't use those. I have found that if you press and hold a second or two, it works more reliably. If you're in a hurry and do a quick tap of the toggle - about 50/50. So don't be in a hurry. The toggle button is orange, but not neon. With the batteries in, they are fairly weighty. Fit in a pocket. Not sure how much more "focused" on the product I can get and additionally honestly reveal my experience. I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful.
UPDATE 10/26/21.... tossed in the bin. Doesn't work at all any more. Super disappointing. I would steer clear as both turned out to be junk.

title: reusable face shield
text: You get 10 reusable face shields.  They are plastic, antifog and have a foam forehead piece with an elastic band that fits snugly to the back of your head. The shield completely covers your face, down below your chin.  I've recently read a couple of other reviews stating that the shields aren't "clear" or too foggy to see through... You need to realize there is a REMOVABLE FILM on the front and inside of the shield!! You need to remove that film from the front and inside of the shield and they are perfectly clear! The film is to keep the shields from sticking to each other and protect from scratching in shipping (my guess).  They are comfortable to wear. You can spray with cleaner and reuse them.  I would definitely purchase these again and actually have.  My first order never arrived - probably due to the mail issues that plague all of us lately. title: battery wall switch
text:
Meh. So, they give you instructions about the battery... but there is a plate (the wall hanging plate- that the instruction do NOT show at all) that I actually had to snap off the back to get to the battery to remove the battery saving tab. What a drag. And now, even though the base is only about 5 ft away from the switch, it only works about 50% of the time. I will probably just toss it when I get frustrated enough about it not working well. I hate to write reviews that are less than 5 star - but occasionally this is going to happen. :(
2/27/2019 - full disclosure - I have been asked to reconsider my original review and have been provided another switch by the seller. Sadly, I have nothing more positive to say about the switch. One of the most disappointing points of this switch is that in order to use the switch you must remove the back plate to access the battery box. The problem I had with the first switch is the same with the second one provided. It simply will not budge. It doesn't slide... it doesn't pop off... it is solidly attached. You must 'force' the plate off, which is plastic, and of course, breaks. So you plan to use it as desk top or table top switch - you're good. However, you won't be able to attach to a wall after breaking the back panel simply to access the battery box. I had the same issues with the second one as with the first, it doesn't work more than it does as a switch. It is a toggle - so you press it over and over again - sometimes it works, sometimes it doesn't. Note: the switch was about 2ft from the receiver - well within the distance specifications. Frustrating to say the least. I really appreciate that the seller is trying to address their production issues. They have been friendly and active. I believe that they are genuinely trying to address all of these issues. I am an Amazon customer for over 25 years - carefully and honestly reviewing thousands of items. It is rare to have a seller so seemingly committed and forthwith in their communication with me. I do wish I had more positive things to say about this switch - but I think their issue is with the makers of these switches - not the seller. I anticipate they will be able to make easy changes in the production - such as not attaching the wall plate before shipping. As for the other issues - sometimes you have work out quality control as well. I thank the seller for contacting me and for seeking out my input as to what the issues are. I just wish I could have changed my review to their benefit.

title: 6ft cherry tree
text:
I ordered this for a plain corner in my semi tiny house and it is perfect... I have included some pics for you to see about the construction and materials. Took about 5 minutes to set up. The flowers are a silicone type material, soft and pliable. The lights are LED and they have a soft white glow. I purchased a switch to turn them on remotely - no on off switch, just a plug in. The tree arrives bent at the top but is about 6 ft tall. *NOTE: in the photo I actually have it standing on small table about 8" tall behind the chair as I wanted the lower branches a bit taller. I love the look of it and the soft glow it gives. It came with spare parts (flowers, etc) which I taped the bag to the base as in my case, you are not going to be looking at the base. The base is a plastic stand you put together, I used the heel of my hand to pound just a bit to get the base made. The tree is wrapped with a dark brown tape that works well in my room with the dark brown leather furniture. As long as it lasts a decent amount of time, I couldn't be happier. A few other notes:
There is a slight plastic smell... in case you're super sensitive.. it hasn't bothered me too much and I think it will dissipate over time... Also, the tree can sort of tip over if you don't the branches balanced out fairly well.. there are 2 pieces and the top portion, with all the branches has a bit of weight to it as you can imagine. Having said all that, I never hesitate to update my review should new info seem useful. I hope this info and the photos were helpful to you!

title: mason jar lights
text:
These are just the lids and lights... NO JARS. I knew this going in, so I purchased my own jars and some polished rocks to use as weights - we have rambunctious ground squirrels. I also purchased, separately, "stainless steel" handles as we live on the ocean front in Oregon. The handles were a bit of trick to get on the jar - it works best if you "screw" them on, like a lid sort of. I sort of twirled the lights so they hung down as a swirl down the center of the jar and then screwed the lids onto the jars. They charge in the day, come on at dusk and mostly stay on all night long. A couple I notice don't.. but I was only hoping for a few hours - so I'm good with this. They are not really bright enough to use a path way light - but they are bright enough to be a very pretty decoration. I ordered a dozen, but went back for a third set as my very determined squirrels did manage to shatter one by knocking it off even with rocks for weights! My Mom loved them, so I let her take three of them. She has them in her window sill, inside. They work nicely there too. As long as they get sun to charge, it's good. Now, I will say, that the rings have become to rust. I haven't tried to pop out the light portion and put a new ring on, but I may try this after the summer season is over. All work. I had NO failures. Some don't last through the night, even though they have exactly the same sun exposure - but still, last for hours. I do recommend putting something in the jars for weights even if you don't have sassy squirrels like we do as they will likely stay put better. ..As I said I used polished rocks.. but you could use glass beads or marbles or shells that heavy or packaged sand (because its dry - don't get it off the beach) really anything that would provide weight and you can fit into the canning jar. All in all, I really like these lights... just wish the rings were more resistant to rust! They would make beautiful wedding decor, or other party decor or individually as gifts with special inserts (weights). My Mom adores hers. I never hesitate to update my reviews should new info seem useful. If I decided to try and replace the rings I will post how that went. And I hope this info was helpful to you in some way.
UPDATE 8/14/2018.... I have added some photos that might be helpful - while the outer rings have rusted... eh... they are outside.. we are oceanfront (although they would rust outdoors anywhere) - I consider the rust "patina" ... I may not attempt to replace the rings until they are not functional anymore - a couple seasons?? I DO recommend the separate purchase of the handles. They make the jars a lot easier to move around. Hope this is helpful to you!

title: Salt lamp bowl
text:
I purchased two of these for my tiny AZ home... one for the master bedroom and one for the living/dining area. I have never purchased a salt lamp before and I cannot speak to the list of possible benefits, but I am hopeful for positive results. However, having said that, the lamp is lovely. The dimmer switch is very nice. You can control the brightest easily using the dimmer switch which clearly changes the mood. The salt chunks are large and each chunk is unique in color and size and shape as you can imagine. The bowl holder is a clear acrylic type material... about 8" in diameter - just eye balling it... and about 6" tall. It came very carefully and beautifully packaged. Once you put the salt in the bowl I can image that you don't want to move them around a lot as it could scratch the bowl. I did carefully move a few pieces to places I felt were better. I have had the lamps plugged in for about 8 hours... no odors. Just a really beautiful glow. The dimmer switch is hard. You just tap it to turn it on or off and gently press to dim or brighten. There is a very nice booklet with instructions on how to change the bulb (a spare is provided) Cleaning instructions say: regularly dust salt crystals with a dry, clean cloth. Do not wash or clean with water or detergents, If not in use for a long period of time, store the lamp in a cool, dry environment, covering the crystals with a plastic bag. The lamp may naturally moisten in humid environments - saying further that if you use in a humid environment leave the lamp on for several hours to naturally dry out (I'm thinking like in a bathroom?) They also note not to place to close to electronics as the salt may draw moisture. It says if the salt crystals become moist - gently pat down with a clean dry cloth - also noting not to clean the bowl with any organic or other solvents or it may become damaged.
I would say if you're looking to purchase one of these as a gift, they are beautifully packaged and look very high end. The price is definitely higher than some of the options but not the highest. I personally chose the bowl style of salt crystal because salt may draw moisture and I wanted it contained instead of dripping off a free standing rock without containment. I do really love the soft glow. That alone is worth the purchase to me. I do really hope the claimed health benefits will be a bonus.
I never hesitate to update my reviews if new info should seem useful. I also try to answer all questions to best of my ability. Hope this helps you in your decision.
UPDATE: 2/10/2017.... I have been using both lamps 24/7 for some weeks now. Both are still working perfectly. I still believe these salt lamps are a really good buy. I've looked at so many in person that were so much more money and so much less lamp. I think one of the best parts is the dimming light. You can really adjust to comfort, for instance, in the bedroom. Still feel these lamps are really 5 star items.

title: SadoTech Model C Waterproof Wireless doorbell
text:
UPDATE BELOW.....Purchased two... I live on the oceanfront and so the "waterproof" part was appealing. I took pics to show what you get in the box. Mine is the white with blue button. I purchased the industrial velcro to attach because I wanted to be able to remove the transmitter when needed for battery or other... The front door transmitter is about 15 feet from the base and rings every time... the back door transmitter is about 20 feet from the base and rings every time. I chose 2 different rings so I could tell which was the back door and which was the front (one of the reasons I purchased 2 units). There is a volume button with 4 volume choices. You will need an outlet to plug in the receiver (the bell). As I just installed these I will be updating with any useful information. So far, they work perfectly. They arrived quickly (I have prime) and in good condition with other items I purchased. I do NOT receive compensation for my reviews of ANY kind.
UPDATE: 6/28/2016.... I have discovered that if the power flickers or goes out, you will need to reset your chime choice. I wish there was switch that would just "set" your choice with a battery backup source (?) However, that would mean it would be probably double in size.. so you just have to keep pushing that chime button until you find your choice again.
